# a)Detect outliers using z score method
data=[1,2,2,2,3,1,1,15,2,2,2,3,1,1,2]
mean=np.mean(data)
std=np.std(data)
threshold=3
outliers=[i for i in data if(i-mean)/std>threshold]
print(" The mean is ",mean)
print(" The Std deviation is ",std)
print(" Outliers in dataset of  Z-Score is ",outliers)

 The mean is  2.6666666666666665
 The Std deviation is  3.3598941782277745
 Outliers in dataset of  Z-Score is  [15]

# b)Detect outliers using IQR method
np.random.seed(102)
data=np.concatenate([[50,52,53,55,60,61,62,65,67]*20,np.random.randint(0,101,size=300)])
Q1,Q3= np.percentile(data,[0.25,0.75])
IQR = Q3 - Q1
ll=Q1-1.5*IQR
ul=Q3+1.5*IQR
outliers_iqr = data[(data < ll) | (data > ul)]
print(" Outliers in dataset of IQR method is ",outliers_iqr)

# h)Treat outliers using Deleting observations. Transforming values (scaling and cube root transformation) and imputation (mean, median and zero)

m = np.mean(data1['Age'])
print('mean:', m)
for i in data1['Age']:
    if i < ll or i > ul:
        data1['Age'] = data1['Age'].replace(i, m)

m = data1['Age'].median()
print("median:", m)
for i in data1['Age']:
    if i < ll or i > ul:
        data1['Age'] = data1['Age'].replace(i, m)

for i in data1['Age']:
    if i < ll or i > ul:
        data1['Age'] = data1['Age'].replace(i, 0)

mean: 31.514115942028983
median: 31.514115942028983

# b) Find number of clusters using Elbow method
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
wcss = []
for i in range(1, 11):
  kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters = i, init = 'k-means++', max_iter = 300, n_init = 10, random_state=102)
  kmeans.fit(x)
  wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)
plt.plot(range(1, 11), wcss)
plt.title('The Elbow Method')
plt.xlabel('No. of Clusters')
plt.ylabel('wcss')
plt.show()

import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow import keras

    keras.layers.Flatten(input_shape=(28, 28)),
    keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),

])
